@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #75961 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?

This issues seems to be related to #69121 (reported on June). Is there something actionable for a discussion? Should someone from the @*WG-mir-opt* have a look at this?
As there seems nothing to be on fire (albeit a regression...) could a P-medium be a good candidate for this issue?
Is this actually a MIR-opt issue? What caused it?
Can't exactly say why, by my limited knowledge I can only say that the compiler bumped in some code it could not generated. Yes, maybe a bisection like you added could help.
Does it need a ping to the cleanup group for that?
based on the same idea, non working code generating an ICE I'd go with P-medium
